President Barack Obama has issued a proclamation recognizing Labor Day and celebrating the contributions of American workers. The proclamation highlights the economic progress made during his presidency, including the creation of 8 million jobs in the past 3 years and a record-breaking streak of 66 straight months of job growth. Obama emphasizes the importance of middle-class economics and the need for policies that support working families, such as a fair minimum wage, overtime pay, and workplace safety laws. The President also calls for the expansion of benefits like paid sick days and family leave, and the right to organize. He concludes by urging Americans to continue working towards a future where everyone is treated fairly and has access to opportunities for success.